title.@value: Overflow incontinence associated with pelvic organ prolapse

definition.@value: A condition of the urinary system, caused by the incomplete emptying of urine from the bladder and an acontractile detrusor muscle. This condition is characterised by urinary incontinence and leakage of urine in small volumes. This condition may be associated with obstruction, weak bladder muscles, injury, pharmacological use, diabetes mellitus, nerve damage or nervous system dysfunction.

label.@value: Overflow incontinence associated with pelvic organ prolapse
